caption: Perfect ramen, nice staff, try the mogu chicken too!

Every time I return to Japan, the number of MAZE SOBA ramen shops is increasing considerably. However, only about 3% offer really delicious MAZE SOBA. This MAZE SOBA store in the United States is only about 35 points, assuming that it has a perfect score of 100 points. If it is Tokyo, it will be defeated at this level.
We had a superb experience in this place. We enjoyed the excellent vibes and the meals. The staff are very personal. I am happy we finally managed to visit this spot.
Delicious mazemen and takoyaki (I love takoyaki). Our waiter was super friendly as well. Ramen is just ok - come here for the mazemen.

Really good authentic japanese food. Even the server and chef is japanese. You can taste the quality and effort. The noodles are very soft and tender. The ingredients are very fresh. Egg is straight from the farm.
Very good flavors! Mazemen was a new dish for me and it did not disappoint. We will return the next time we are in the area.

We like a lot hanging out. Yesterday we came to this fine restaurant which friends told us about. We had a beautiful experience there with very good food and a well-trained stuff and a distinguished  cuisine. We put this fine restaurant in our phone list  and we shall surely return soon. We deeply recommend.

I have been in this restaurant a few times after the previous terrible review.  The food has gotten a lot better. I like this place because they made the udon on site. The udon noodle is fresh. Over all, the food quality has been stable.
Service was great, the noodles were beyond delicious!
Really good, fast and really affordable
Good food !!
The portions are bigger than they look.

I come to this excellent restaurant from time to time because I love the good mood that is part of this place. The personel is awfuly cordial and skilfull. The service is extremely fast. Most important, the food they cook is good. I …
The noodle texture is unreal. Just perfectly chewy. Travels surprisingly well for takeout (eggs are packaged separately).

Mazemen is taking LA by storm, and it all started with Mogumogu. Today I had the Deluxe Mazemen with chashu and a seasoned egg. They have sidewalk seating now so you can eat in during covid. Beautiful presentation when it arrives  First you …

Not only was this place insanely delicious, the staff is incredibly friendly and helpful. The food itself is amazing - I was in LA for a week trying new restaurants for every meal and this place holds my #1 spot for favorite thing I ate! Definitely recommend!!
Delicious mazemen. go for the deluxe. Hands down, one of the best ramen I have had. Different from the traditional ramen.
The Tokyo was incredible. The instructions on how to best enjoy are extremely good. So freaking good. Can not recommend more.
First-time tried soup less ramen. It is actually pretty good. I was surprised how good it is. Although I still prefer the ramen soup, I would recommend to try it out.
Not sure take-out is good for this place... they do a great job telling you how to get the best experience, but nothing beats a piping hot bowl of mazemen's super thick noodles eaten in.

Some of the best ramen I've found in SF: umami-rich broth with excellent thin noodles and all the fixins. Get the deluxe whether you go for pork or chicken. Interior is very nicely done and modern with great lighting and without being too loud. Super fast service cause there's a hundred more people in line after you!

This place is across the street from my office and I eat here once a week. I LOVE the basic Tokyo.So delicious. And the people are so nice.  I have been ordering dinner from here while in quarantine. Also delicious. Though you do have to race home to eat it while it's hot - still totally worth it.

My Japanese friend in LA told me about this place, so I went there with him and totally loved it. It's a nice little place, filled with young people mostly, enjoying their ramen... The staff is super friendly, decoration on the wall is cool and the food is delicious. Doesn't matter what you order there, you will be happy with it for sure

My girlfriend gets Mogumogu delivered as often as she can, which means I've had it more than I care to admit. But even after bowls on bowls of mazemen, I still really enjoy it.  The original aka tokyo style mazemen is what I recommend most …
Don't let the outside area fool you. Inside is very clean and inviting. Very yummy food and great service!
Noodles with an intricate balance of tase. Extremely tasty with an acceptable price. Quick eatery for delicious noodles.

I normally reserve 5 star for places I'm a regular, but in the words of Gordon Ramsay "FUHHK MEEE"! This place was amazing.  I never knew there were different styles or Ramen. What I had was called Mazemen.  I was told it means or is "dry …
It was delicious and the staff was friendly and funny!! I ordered the deluxe! So delicious! I can’t wait to go back and try the cheese one!

First time trying soupless ramen, and it was amazing! I thought it’d be too salty like many ramens are (Tsujita) but the seasoning was great, and with the mixing of rice at the end of your meal, I walked away from Mogumogu very full and …

Tried the cheese mazeman (dry noodles with various toppings with some soup at the bottom) and it was great.  Noodles were nice and chewy.  Long waits on Friday evening, get on the waitlist before you go.
The mazemen (dry ramen) is delicious and one of a kind!
Delicious!

The ramen here was good, but not great. Not sure why it's so popular. Maybe because it's more convenient for people to come here than go to Sawtelle? Restaurant is small and seating is limited, just like their parking lot that they share with the gym and print shop next door. Wait staff is nice and overall feel is casual.
Amazing food, had some new experiences for me
I get the deluxe. I can't think of anything else like it, and it's wonderful. If you like ramen, but maybe way less soup definitely give this place a shot. Perfect eggs, c'mon.

What a pleasant surprise. I'm not about to anoint these guys the ramen king of sawtelle, and Tsujita still might have an edge, but no hassle with lines, super reasonably priced, and such unique flavors! Stoked!

Small ramen and mazemen restaurant close to Sawtelle. Came here on a Saturday for lunch with a friend around 1pm. Surprisingly there was no wait time, but you can also get on the waitlist through Yelp. There’s a machine where you can put …
My wife and I love this place.  We can't get enough.  All the dishes are amazing but my favorite is the curry with the cheese.  This is the closest Mazemen you will find to what they serve in Japan.
Amazing flavor!!! Great portion. Small place with a lot of flavor. Truly a must place to visit.

This is a gem. If you like a big blend of umami flavors in a magical bowl of noodles then this place will change your life. Mogu mogu chicken and buns are fantastic but this place is all about the noodle magic. Don't forget the Mexican coke to wash it all down.

I was there with my friends last night the staff was extremely friendly. I was there with a group of 7 friends whom I meet with regularly but we ended up staying for a bit longer than an hour and there was no rush or anything.
Mogu Mogu was absolutely delish. The Tokyo style ramen was my choice. Along with a side of the fried chicken. Both very very good!! I will be back!
Insanely good food and a very unique noodle experience. Flavors were outstanding! Service was friendly and to notch, for sure going again

Tokyo mazemen is good and not too salty. I like the chewy noodles! It comes with a scoop of rice that you can add to the sauce after finishing the noodles. The spicy chili sauce, which I think may contain sesame oil, is good as well.
Deluxe was delicious!!! Will be back again :)

Mogumogu is a great place for a fine noodles fans, they have a great chef,  very nice staff and Tomo "the creator" of that place is wonderful, I had the chance to meet him and Rick, both awesome guys, everyone should try the food in this amazing restaurant.

Soupless ramen or mazemen is such a nice change of pace. This is like eating 2.5 dishes in one. First you mix the noodles and ingredients and taste the rich deep flavor. To change the flavor add a bit of their housemade umami vinegar. When …
The place always packed because of the new style of soupless ramen. It is very good and unique way to enjoy it.
Great service and great quality food.

For the price and quality it is definitely one of the decent restaurants. The ajitama is just perfectly boiled and pickled. They give you some rice to finish the soup after you finish your mazenoodles which can be very satisfying.

Awesome noodle place, the vibe is hip.  Staff was awesome. Loved chatting with the guy working the cashier!  Support new local businesses!!! It's so important.  I had the signature bowl. It was very filling. The flavors were good and I …

This place is solid ramen. You can get on the yelp waitlist which is great since they don't take reservations. The ramen broth is hearty and what I imagine Japan's ramen broth to be like. The meat and tender and the price is cheap since it …
Exploding with flavor. Mazemen is new to me and  I loved it, had the Deluxe which was a lot of food. Definitely recommend trying it out. Staff was friendly and quick to help.
My only hesitation in reviewing Mogumogu is that next time I might have to wait longer. This Curry Mazemen is a 10/10

Tasty and hearty meal.  I haven't had this particular style of noodles before, but on a recommendation from my Japanese friend, we were excited to try this new place out.  We tried the Deluxe, the karaage, and both types of buns. We loved it all.

Refreshing addition to Sawtelle ramen scene. If you like tsujita, then you'll like the fish powder that gets added as a dry topping. I usually ask for it on the side since I find it a bit overpowering. Service is slow usually because of the kitchen. Vegan ramen is a nice lighter alternative.

Good noodles but really disappointing Ramen. The Tonkotsu I ordered had nothing in common with any Tonkotsu I have had up until now. The broth was thin, tasted a bit bitter and was probably the most disappointing I've ever had. I know this …
Great little spot. Reminded me of a less soupier tsukemen, the taste was great!

Ordered the deluxe bowl of mazemen as well as the mogu chicken. Both were delicious. Since I am a person that does not always eat all the broth in regular ramen, mazemen is an excellent alternative. All of the flavor, chewy noodles and less liquid.
Incredibly tasty twist on what you ramen is. Worth the visit.
Super delicious! Stood up to the hype. I would definitely come back! I had the deluxe bowl and I loved every bite and I can’t wait to have it again.
It's a nice atmosphere ended up paying cash because the credit card machines down mazemen is their popular dish not bad  you can even watch anime in the background
My first time there today for lunch and it won’t be the last! I tried out the Tokyo and love it.
Never added rice to leftover noodle sauce before but wow yummy. Adding vinegar makes it more refreshing! Yum

Sawtelle continues to be the ramen mecca of all of LA and just as I thought the area couldn’t get better… in comes Mogumogu.  Mogumogu's addition of Mazemen adds a fresh air to Tsujita's tsukemen, Annex's miso ramen, and Killer noodle's …

Best mazemen I've had in the US yet. Great chewy noodles, awesome sauce but I did not like the kale at all (doesn't fit in ramen) and would've preferred non-spicy minced pork since the sauce is already seasoned and spicy. I'd definitely come back though.
Love it

Delicious ramen here! I got the deluxe bowl and it was pretty filling. It had great flavors, a bit of a spiciness to it but not too hot. I really liked the noodles.. really good texture and bite to it. Definitely a great ramen spot. It's a bit small so can get crowded during peak hours.
The first time i had abura soba in america! They did not disappoint! :)
Had the Tokyo Mazemen, it was fantastic. Perfectly cooked noodles and wonderful flavor. I'll definitely be back.
Good appetizers and ramen with a good price point. A good lunch spot.

This place serves an amazing bowl of ramen (pictured: The Deluxe) at a good price.  It's a lot less oily than your typical bowl of ramen, which means it doesn't weigh so heavily on your stomach, but the flavor is still superb.  The rice …

WOW. WOW. WOW. I'm speechless. I may have found my new favorite noodle spot in LA  I just stumbled upon this restaurant while browsing yelp for a new noodle joint to try And it soooOooo happened to be the last day of the Grand Opening …

The food was amazing and five stars to the service . I got me their simple spicy Ramen soup, but it was so great tasting and the noodles were off the chain perfect. I so recommend this place... I did not take a picture because I was focused on how awesome my bowl looked. Perfect after work meal!
First time eating a "soup-less" ramen...delicious! Photo of the Deluxe

Look out Sawtelle, mogummogu is coming. This Japanese treat brought savory joy into my belly. Great service, animé I'm the background, suitable background music. Thrilled that we have another great option in LA. Thank you!
I like maze soba of this ramen place.
This place is so good! Love the noodles
Fantastic and so delicious! Will be a regular here
delicious, plain and simple
Get any of the Mazemen and follow the tips on the wall for the best experience!

Have you heard Mazemen Ramen Noodle?  Me either and this is a ramen that doesn't have a soup but all other delicious toppings and noodles. But it is not Tsukemen. I believe there is no other restaurant around here offer something like this. …

Taste(5/5) Price $ Service(5/5) Interior(5/5)  HIGHLY RECOMMENDED  *Cheese Mazemen (5/5) - Taste is so GOOD. It is not traditional ramen. It is ramen without soup. There are several minced ingredients, green onions, garlic, pork, fish …
